By brand, inventories ending the quarter at Justice were $101 million, an increase of 20% versus last year. We were pleased with the strong May-to-date sales results that David mentioned from both stores and e-commerce which have lowered these levels. Justice inventory levels are expected to decrease to the low teens by the end of the fourth quarter.
Inventory ending the quarter at maurices was $73 million, an increase of 24%. This inventory increase supports the strong sales trends that maurices experienced during the quarter, up 17%.
At dressbarn, inventories ended the quarter at $127 million, a 5% increase versus last year, in line with recent sales trends.
