On the second question, Brian, the e-commerce channel in general tends to be a more profitable channel on a margin basis than brick-and-mortar. And if you think about it, you don't have to pay sales help and you don't have to pay rent. So you've got other expenses, obviously, but that's a big difference. And all things being run equally, you should see a better margin.
And indeed, we've got some history at Justice. We are seeing very strong margins.
 
 
