Our profit growth has generated strong cash flows which have been invested back into our business. Our philosophy under uses of our cash, first are to invest and grow our businesses. Second, to either selectively make strategic acquisitions or buy back shares. We believe this approach delivers the best returns to our shareholders. During the past three years, we've invested $317 million in capital spending primarily for stores and information systems. Over the long term, we expect over a half our capital to be invested in stores as stores represent one of our highest returns. The fiscal 2013, we are planning to spend $325 million, as well as planning to make a $50 million payment against our outstanding $300 million term loan.
 
